SIMPLE: inability
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inability
<hw>In`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>ability</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>inhabilet⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Able</er>, and cf.
<er>Unable</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being unable; lack
of ability; lack of sufficient power, strength, resources, or
capacity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is not from an <qex>inability</qex> to discover what they ought
to do, that men err in practice.</q> <rj><qau>Blair.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impotence; incapacity; incompetence; weakness;
powerlessness; incapability. See <er>Disability</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inable</ent>⟦br⟧
